metadata.name: Glomularus #211
metadata.description:
Glomularus is an exploration in generative, artificial life forms. The project is an extension of my Protobyte series, begun in 2004.

Driven by Verlet icosahedra and responsive tendrils, Glomulari live in a spherical virtual ecosystem (V-eco) enhanced through user interaction.

Interaction:

Mouse/Trackpad:
  drag -> camera rotation
  drag + CMD/CTR -> camera pan
  scroll wheel/pinch -> camera zoom

Key Input:
  1-9: add acceleration
  -, +: reduce | increase V-eco sphere radius
  f, g: reduce | increase fog
  p: screen capture

Tip:
To decrease creature acceleration, reduce V-eco sphere radius

Note:
Please post your favorite Glomularus screen captures
TW: @iragreenberg
IG: @greenberg.ira

Built with Three.js, PByte.js, TypeScript, Node

metadata.name: Rigveda Mandala #2
metadata.description: A large number of particles, chosen randomly, are rotated in space according to a sine-based function. Colour is chosen according to angle, direction and the given hash. There is a small chance of a narrow-radius, circular mandala, and a greater chance of a pouring, changing flow of particles from the centre outwards. The movement is controlled by three parameters of varying size.

metadata.name: impressions 04 #208
metadata.description:
The final of four impressions, an exercise in pulling discernible patterns from utter chaos. 

Palette - One of 10 different color palettes.
Shape - Is the source an ellipse or a square?
Divisions - The X/Y resolution of the pattern.
xRand & yRand - the X and Y dimensions of each element.

metadata.name: Moonlit Sea #96
metadata.description:
A few years ago, my son and I went on a long-term trip to Taitung, Taiwan. One night on the roof of the B&B, we saw the moonlight falling on the pacific ocean. It was very beautiful and peaceful. We will never forget this scene.

Made with memory and p5js.

Variables:
- 24 palettes + random colors
- 5 moon shapes
- 2 island patterns
- 5 wave strength

Control(in live view):
- Press [s] to save a high-res png image

metadata.name: Disegnatori #47
metadata.description:
Each disegnatore learns a different portion of a city map, looking at it stroke by stroke and creating a probabilistic Markov model of the sequences of relative angles and distances, tracing the outline of each building in that portion of the map. This way, each disegnatore has a different internal understanding of the city.

It then starts from the middle of the canvas and wanders out, stroke by stroke, probability by probability, trying not to intersect any previously drawn outlines and avoiding the edges of the canvas until a predetermined number of edges have been drawn.

The Markov chain drawing model is created during execution from a text file representation of a city map.

Open live to see your disegnatore drawing or to resize.
